'''Mazeltov''' is a [[Yiddish]] word meaning "good luck" but is often used in place of "congratulations."  Like other [[blessings]] it is often said frequently and sometimes loudly at [[Jewish]] [[weddings]] as well as [[Bar Mitzvah]]s.  It is commonly used within the Jewish community.  In colloquial languange, "Mazel tov" is sometimes said sarcastically when congratulations are not appropriate or due.

